    "instruction": "Implement an algorithm to check if two strings are one edit away.",
    "input": "",
    "output": "def is_one_edit_away(s1, s2):\n # Check if lengths are more than one character difference\n if abs(len(s1) - len(s2)) > 1:\n  return False\n \n # Get shorter and longer strings\n shorter = s1 if len(s1) < len(s2) else s2\n longer = s1 if len(s1) > len(s2) else s2\n \n i = 0\n j = 0\n edit_count = 0\n \n while i < len(shorter) and j < len(longer):\n  if shorter[i] != longer[j]:\n   if edit_count == 1:\n    return False\n   \n   # if lengths are unequal, move shorter pointer\n   if len(shorter) != len(longer):\n    i += 1\n   else:\n    i += 1\n    j += 1\n   \n   edit_count += 1\n\n # move longer pointer\n if i < len(shorter):\n  j += 1\n\n return edit_count == 1",
    "category": "code_instruction"
