    "instruction": "Produce a Ruby module to perform some basic statistics on an array of numbers.",
    "input": "[1, 2, 4, 9, 5]",
    "output": "module Statistics\n  # Return the sum of an array of numbers\n  def self.sum(arr)\n    arr.inject(0, :+)\n  end\n\n  # Return the mean of an array of numbers\n  def self.mean(arr)\n    sum = Statistics.sum(arr)\n    sum.to_f / arr.length\n  end\n\n  # Return the variance of an array of numbers\n  def self.variance(arr)\n    mean = Statistics.mean(arr)\n    sum_squares = arr.inject(0) { |sum, x| sum + (x - mean) ** 2 } \n    sum_squares.to_f / arr.length\n  end\nend",
