    "output": "# C Program to generate a random password string \n# with specified requirements \n\n#include <stdio.h>\n#include <stdlib.h>\n#include <time.h>\n\n// This function generates random passwords \nchar* random_password(int length) \n{   \n    int i; \n    char* password = malloc(length * sizeof(char)); \n    int count; \n  \n    const char lowercase_characters[] = \n\t\t\"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz\"; \n    const char uppercase_characters[] = \n\t\t\"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"; \n    const char numerals[] = \"0123456789\"; \n    const char special_characters[] = \"+-*/!@#$^&?()<>{}[]:,~\"; \n  \n    while (count < length) { \n        i = rand() % 4; \n        switch (i) { \n        case 0: \n            password[count] = lowercase_characters[rand() % \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t26]; \n            break; \n        case 1: \n            password[count] = uppercase_characters[rand() % \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t26]; \n            break; \n        case 2: \n            password[count] = numerals[rand() % 10]; \n            break; \n        case 3: \n            password[count] = special_characters[rand() % 15]; \n            break; \n        } \n        count++; \n    } \n  \n    return password; \n} \n  \n// Driver code \nint main(void) \n{ \n    int length = 8; \n  \n    char* pswd; \n    pswd = random_password(length); \n    printf(\"Random Password : %s\\n\", pswd);\n    free(pswd); \n  \n    return 0; \n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
