    "instruction": "Implement an algorithm in C++ to search an array of floats and find the value closest to a given target value.",
    "input": "arr = [1.2, 3.4, 5.6, 7.8], target = 4.5",
    "output": "#include <iostream>\n#include <cmath>\n\nusing namespace std;\n\n// Function to find the closest value to the target\nfloat findClosest(float arr[], int n, float target)\n{\n    // Initialize closest value\n    float closest = arr[0];\n\n    // Start loop from 1\n    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++)\n    {\n        // Check if current value is closer than \n        // previous value\n        float diff = abs(target - arr[i]);\n        if (abs(target - closest) > diff)\n            closest = arr[i];\n    }\n \n    return closest;\n}\n\n// Driver program to test above function\nint main()\n{\n    float arr[] = { 1.2, 3.4, 5.6, 7.8};\n    int n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);\n    float target = 4.5;\n    cout << findClosest(arr, n, target);\n \n    return 0;\n}",
