    "instruction": "Generate an algorithm to detect the language of a given string.",
    "input": "",
    "output": "def detect_language(str): \n    # Get the length of the string\n    n = len(str)\n    \n    # Initialize a dictionary to store the count of characters in the string\n    charsDict = {}\n    for i in range(n): \n        ch = str[i] \n        \n        # If the character is not present in the dictionary\n        # add it to the dictionary\n        if ch not in charsDict: \n            charsDict[ch] = 1\n        else:\n        # increment the count of the character\n        charsDict[ch] += 1\n  \n    # Find the most frequent \n    maxx = -1\n    maxChar = ''\n  \n    # Iterate through all characters in characters dictionary\n    for ch in charsDict: \n        if maxx < charsDict[ch]: \n            maxx = charsDict[ch] \n            maxChar = ch \n  \n    # The most frequent character is the first character of the language of the string\n    lang = chr(ord(maxChar) - ord('a') + ord('A'))\n    \n    # Return the language\n    return lang",
    "category": "code_instruction"
