    "instruction": "Write a C code to create a matrix of given dimensions.",
    "input": "Rows: 3\nColumns: 4",
    "output": "#include <stdio.h> \n\n// Function to create a matrix \nvoid createMatrix(int row, int col, int matrix[row][col]) \n{ \n    int i, j; \n\n    // Get the matrix elements \n    for (i = 0; i < row; i++) \n    { \n        for (j = 0; j < col; j++) \n        { \n            printf(\"Enter element m[%d][%d]: \", i, j);\n            scanf(\"%d\", &matrix[i][j]); \n        } \n    } \n} \n\n// Print the matrix \nvoid printMatrix(int row, int col, int matrix[row][col]) \n{ \n    int i, j; \n\n    // Print the matrix \n    for (i = 0; i < row; i++) \n    { \n        for (j = 0; j < col; j++) \n        { \n            printf(\"%d  \", matrix[i][j]); \n            if (j == col - 1) \n                printf(\"\\n\"); \n        } \n    } \n} \n\nint main() \n{ \n    int rows, cols;\n  \n    // Get the row and column size \n    printf(\"Enter the rows and cols size: \");\n    scanf(\"%d%d\", &rows, &cols);\n      \n    int arr[rows][cols]; \n  \n    // Create the matrix \n    createMatrix(rows, cols, arr); \n  \n    // Printing the matrix \n    printMatrix(rows, cols, arr); \n      \n    return 0; \n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
