    "instruction": "Write a TensorFlow program that takes a string of text as input and classifies it as spam or not spam.",
    "input": "\"LIMITED TIME OFFER! Get 50% off on your order!\"",
    "output": "import tensorflow as tf\n\n#data\nspam_data = [\n    \"LIMITED TIME OFFER! Get 50% off on your order!\",\n    \"It's time to take control of your health. Get 50% off on our supplements today!\"\n]\nnot_spam_data = [\n    \"Welcome to your weekly business update. Here's what's happening this week...\",\n    \"Check out our new article on the importance of sleep. Get your daily doses of rest!\"\n]\n\n#labels\nlabels = [1,1,0,0]\n\n#pre-processing\ntokenizer = tf.keras.preprocessing.text.Tokenizer(num_words=1000)\ntokenizer.fit_on_texts(spam_data + not_spam_data)\ndata = tokenizer.texts_to_matrix(spam_data + not_spam_data, mode='tfidf')\n\nmodel = tf.keras.Sequential()\nmodel.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(16, input_shape=(1000,), activation='relu'))\nmodel.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(8, activation='relu'))\nmodel.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))\n\nmodel.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])\n\n#fit\nmodel.fit(data, labels, batch_size=4, epochs=5)\n\n#predict\ndata = tokenizer.texts_to_matrix([\"LIMITED TIME OFFER! Get 50% off on your order!\"], mode='tfidf')\npredictions = model.predict(data)\nprint(predictions)",
