    "instruction": "Sort the list of numbers using a merge sort algorithm.",
    "input": "nums = [3, 9, 4, 5, 0, 8, 1]",
    "output": "def merge_sort(nums):\n    if len(nums) == 1:\n        return nums\n    mid = len(nums) // 2\n    left = merge_sort(nums[:mid])\n    right = merge_sort(nums[mid:])\n    return merge(left, right)\n\ndef merge(left, right):\n    result = []\n    while left and right:\n        if left[0] < right[0]:\n            result.append(left.pop(0))\n        else:\n            result.append(right.pop(0))\n    result.extend(left + right)\n    return result\n\nresult = merge_sort([3, 9, 4, 5, 0, 8, 1])\nprint(result)",
