    "instruction": "Implement an algorithm to find the two shortest strings in an array.",
    "input": "arr = [\"wordpress\", \"drupal\", \"facebook\", \"twitter\"]",
    "output": "def ShortestStrings(arr):\n    shortest = arr[0]\n    second_shortest = arr[1]\n    if len(arr[1]) < len(arr[0]): \n        shortest = arr[1]\n        second_shortest = arr[0] \n    for s in arr:\n        if len(s) < len(shortest):\n            second_shortest = shortest\n            shortest = s \n        elif (len(s) < len(second_shortest) and len(shortest) != len(second_shortest)): \n            second_shortest = s \n    return shortest, second_shortest\n  \narr = [\"wordpress\", \"drupal\", \"facebook\", \"twitter\"]\n\nshortest, second_shortest = ShortestStrings(arr)\nprint(shortest)\nprint(second_shortest)",
    "category": "code_instruction"
