    "instruction": "Create a program to take two strings and generate an edit distance score between them.",
    "input": "str1 = \"Saturday\"\nstr2 = \"Sundays\"",
    "output": "def edit_distance(str1, str2): \n    m = len(str1) \n    n = len(str2)\n    dp = [[0 for x in range(n + 1)] for x in range(m + 1)]\n    for i in range(m + 1): \n        for j in range(n + 1): \n            if i == 0: \n                dp[i][j] = j\n            elif j == 0: \n                dp[i][j] = i\n            elif str1[i - 1] == str2[j - 1]: \n                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1]\n            else: \n                dp[i][j] = 1 + min(dp[i][j - 1],\n                                   dp[i - 1][j],\n                                   dp[i - 1][j - 1])\n    return dp[m][n]",
    "category": "code_instruction"
