    "instruction": "From a given linked list of integers, write a C++ function that finds the median value.",
    "input": "Input Linked List: 10 → 8 → 6 → 15 → 12",
    "output": "#include <iostream>\n\n// A linked list node\nstruct Node\n{\n int data;\n Node* next;\n};\n\n/* Function to find median of a linked list*/\nfloat findMedian(Node *head)\n{\n // Base case\n if (head == NULL)\n return 0;\n\n Node* slow = head;\n Node* fast = head;\n\n while (fast->next != NULL && fast->next->next != NULL)\n {\n fast = fast->next->next;\n slow = slow->next;\n }\n\n if (fast->next == NULL)\n return slow->data;\n\n return (slow->data + slow->next->data) / 2.0;\n}\n\n// A utility function to create a new node\nNode *newNode(int data)\n{\n struct Node *temp = new Node;\n temp->data = data;\n temp->next = NULL;\n return temp;\n}\n\n/* Driver program to run above code */\nint main()\n{\n Node *head = newNode(10);\n head->next = newNode(8);\n head->next->next = newNode(6);\n head->next->next->next = newNode(15);\n head->next->next->next->next = newNode(12);\n\n printf(\"Median is %f\", findMedian(head));\n\n return 0;\n}\n\n// Output: 10.5  (median of the given linked list 10, 8, 6, 15, 12)",
