    "instruction": "Create a C program to find the maximum difference between any two array elements such that larger number appears after the smaller number",
    "input": "The array is [2, 5, 1, 7, 3, 9, 5]",
    "output": "#include <stdio.h> \n\n// function to calculate max difference \nint maxDifference(int arr[], int n) { \n    int maxDiff = -1;    // Initialize Result\n  \n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n        for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {\n  \n            // Find the maximum difference \n            if (arr[j] - arr[i] > maxDiff) {\n\t\tmaxDiff = arr[j] - arr[i]; \n            } \n        } \n    } \n  \n    return maxDiff; \n}  \n  \n// Driver Program to test above function \nint main() { \n    int arr[] = {2, 5, 1, 7, 3, 9, 5}; \n    int n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]); \n    printf(\"Maximum difference is %d\\n\", maxDifference(arr, n)); \n   \n    return 0; \n}",
