    "output": "def calculate_num_cubes(outer_dim):\n    # outer_dim is the outer dimension of the hollow cube\n    # This algorithm contains three steps:\n    # 1. Calculate the volume of the hollow cube\n    volume = outer_dim**3\n    \n    # 2. Calculate the volume of a single cube with side length 1 meter\n    cube_vol = 1**3\n    \n    # 3. Divide the volume of the cube by the volume of a single cube to determine the number of cubes\n    num_cubes = volume // cube_vol\n    \n    return num_cubes",
