    "input": "Message: 'Hello world!'\nKey: 3",
    "output": "# Create a function that encrypts a message using a given key\n\ndef encrypt(message, key):\n    # Create an empty output string\n    output = \"\"\n    \n    # Loop through characters of the message\n    for char in message:\n        # Get the ascii code of the character\n        ascii_code = ord(char)\n        # Encrypt each character by adding the key to the \n        # ascii code\n        encrypted_char = chr(ascii_code + key)\n        # Append the encrypted character to the output string\n        output += encrypted_char\n        \n    return output\n\n# Now call the function with the given parameters\nmessage = 'Hello world!'\nkey = 3\nresult = encrypt(message, key)\n\nprint(\"Encrypted message:\", result)",
