    "instruction": "Develop an artificial intelligence algorithm to optimally solve a sliding-tile puzzle.",
    "input": "A 3 x 3 sliding-tile puzzle",
    "output": "def solve_puzzle(start, goal):\n # Create a dictionary to store the path cost from start node to goal node\n cost = {}\n \n # Initializing the cost of starting node to 0\n cost[start] = 0\n \n # Create a priority queue to store the unexplored nodes\n queue = PriorityQueue()\n \n # Initialize the waiting list with starting node\n queue.put(start, 0)\n \n # Loop until queue is empty or goal is reached\n while not queue.empty():\n # Get the next node from the queue\n current_node = queue.get()\n \n # Check if goal is reached\n if current_node == goal:\n return reconstruct_path(cost, goal)\n \n # Get the neighbors of the current_node\n neighbors = get_neighbors(current_node)\n \n # Iterate over each neighbor\n for neighbor in neighbors:\n # Calculate the cost from starting node to this neighbor\n new_cost = cost[current_node] + get_cost(neighbor, goal)\n \n # Check if the cost to this neighbor is less than the cost stored earlier\n if neighbor not in cost.keys() or new_cost < cost[neighbor]:\n # Update the cost of this neighbor\n cost[neighbor] = new_cost\n # Update previous node and add to the priority queue\n queue.put(neighbor, new_cost)",
