    "instruction": "Generate a C# program to check the validity of a given password string.",
    "input": "",
    "output": "public static bool isValidPassword(string str) \n{ \n    int n = str.Length; \n  \n    // Length should be between 6 and 12 \n    if (n < 6 || n > 12) \n        return false; \n  \n    // Count digits, uppercase and lowercase \n    int cdigit = 0, clcase = 0, cupcase = 0; \n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) \n    { \n        // If a digit, then increment \n        // digit counter \n        if (char.IsDigit(str[i])) \n            cdigit++; \n  \n        // If lowercase character, then \n        // increment lowercase counter \n        else if (char.IsLower(str[i])) \n            clcase++; \n  \n        // If uppercase character, then \n        // increment uppercase counter \n        else if (char.IsUpper(str[i])) \n            cupcase++; \n    } \n  \n    // If digit, lowercase and uppercase \n    // count is more than 0 \n    if (cdigit >= 1 && clcase >= 1 \n        && cupcase >= 1) \n        return true; \n    else \n        return false; \n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
