    "instruction": "Design a program to check whether a given set of strings are anagrams of each other or not.",
    "input": "",
    "output": "# Function to check if two strings are anagrams \ndef is_anagram(str1, str2): \n    # Get the length of both strings \n    n1 = len(str1) \n    n2 = len(str2) \n  \n    # If lengths are not same, then strings are not anagrams \n    if n1 != n2: \n        return False\n  \n    # Sort both strings \n    str1 = sorted(str1) \n    str2 = sorted(str2) \n  \n    # Compare sorted strings \n    for i in range(0, n1): \n        if str1[i] != str2[i]: \n            return False\n  \n    return True\n  \n# Driver program to check above functions \nstrings = [\"abcd\", \"dcba\", \"cde\", \"edc\"]\n\nanagrams = True\n\n# Iterate through each pair of strings \nfor i in range(len(strings)): \n    for j in range(i+1, len(strings)):\n        # Check if the strings are anagrams\n        if not is_anagram(strings[i], strings[j]): \n            anagrams = False\n            break\n          \nif anagrams:\n    print(\"The strings are anagrams of each other.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"The strings are not anagrams of each other.\")",
