    "instruction": "Develop an Android application for a recipe database. This application should include models for Recipe (with fields for the name, ingredients, and instructions) and a RecipeAdapter, which converts the Recipes into a format that can be displayed in a ListView.",
    "input": "Not applicable",
    "output": "public class Recipe {\n private String name;\n private String[] ingredients;\n private String[] instructions;\n \n public Recipe(String name, String[] ingredients, String[] instructions) {\n  this.name = name;\n  this.ingredients = ingredients;\n  this.instructions = instructions;\n }\n \n // Getters and setters\n public String getName() {\n  return name;\n }\n public void setName(String name) {\n  this.name = name;\n }\n public String[] getIngredients() {\n  return ingredients;\n }\n public void setIngredients(String[] ingredients) {\n  this.ingredients = ingredients;\n }\n public String[] getInstructions() {\n  return instructions;\n }\n public void setInstructions(String[] instructions) {\n  this.instructions = instructions;\n }\n}\n\npublic class RecipeAdapter extends ArrayAdapter<Recipe> {\n public RecipeAdapter(@NonNull Context context, List<Recipe> recipes) {\n  super(context, 0, recipes); \n }\n \n @Override\n public View getView(int position, @Nullable View convertView, @NonNull ViewGroup parent) {\n  // Get the data item for this position \n  Recipe recipe = getItem(position);\n  \n  // Check if an existing view is being reused, otherwise inflate the view\n  if (convertView == null) {\n   convertView = LayoutInflater.from(getContext()).inflate(R.layout.list_item, parent, false);\n  }\n  \n  // Lookup view for data population\n  TextView tvName = (TextView) convertView.findViewById(R.id.list_item_name);\n  TextView tvIngredients = (TextView) convertView.findViewById(R.id.list_item_ingredients);\n  \n  // Populate the data into the template view using the data object\n  tvName.setText(recipe.getName());\n  tvIngredients.setText(Arrays.toString(recipe.getIngredients()));\n  \n  // Return the completed view to render onscreen\n  return convertView;\n }\n}",
