    "output": "def getLongestIncreasingSubsequence(arr): \n    n = len(arr) \n  \n    # T[i] stores the length of longest increasing subsequecne \n    # that ends with arr[i] \n    T = [1 for _ in range(n)] \n  \n    for i in range(1, n): \n        for j in range(i): \n            if (arr[i] > arr[j]) and (T[i] < T[j] + 1): \n                T[i] = T[j]+1\n    return max(T) \n\n# example\narr = [10,22,9,33,21,50,41,60,80]\nresult = getLongestIncreasingSubsequence(arr) \nprint (\"Length of longest increasing subsequence is\", result)",
