    "input": "[4, 2, 6, 5, 9, 1, 3]",
    "output": "def bubble_sort(lst): \n    '''This function sorts a given list of numbers in ascending order using bubble sort algorithm'''\n    # Get the length of the list\n    n = len(lst) \n  \n    # Iterate from the end\n    for i in range(n-1): \n        # Swapping values if they are out of order\n        for j in range(0, n-i-1): \n            if lst[j] > lst[j+1] : \n                lst[j], lst[j+1] = lst[j+1], lst[j] \n  \n    # Return the sorted list\n    return lst \n\nInput: [4, 2, 6, 5, 9, 1, 3]\nOutput: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 9]",
