    "input": "Example of a credit card number",
    "output": "public static boolean validateCardNumber(String creditCardNumber) {\n  // Check if the length of the credit card number is valid\n  if (creditCardNumber.length() != 16)\n   return false;\n  \n  // Initialize variables\n  int sum = 0;\n  boolean alternate = false;\n  \n  // Iterate over every digit in the credit card number \n  for (int i = creditCardNumber.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n   int n = Integer.parseInt(creditCardNumber.substring(i, i + 1));\n   \n   // Double every alternate digits \n   if (alternate)\n    n *= 2;\n   \n   // Add the digits in the doubled value\n   if (n > 9)\n    n = (n % 10) + 1;\n   \n   // Add the double digit to the sum\n   sum += n;\n   alternate = !alternate;\n  }\n  \n  // Return true if the sum is a multiple of 10\n  return (sum % 10 == 0);\n}",
