    "instruction": "Generate a program that takes a matrix and identifies the largest square sub-matrix with all 1s.",
    "input": "Given a matrix x =\n[[1, 0, 1],\n[1, 1, 1], \n[0, 1, 1]]",
    "output": "def get_max_square_matrix(x):\n    rows = len(x)\n    cols = len(x[0])\n    \n    result = [[0 for _ in range(cols)] for _ in range(rows)]\n\n    for i in range(rows): \n        result[i][0] = x[i][0]  \n  \n    for i in range(cols): \n        result[0][i] = x[0][i] \n  \n    for i in range(1, rows): \n        for j in range(1, cols): \n            if (x[i][j] == 1):\n                result[i][j] =min(result[i][j-1], result[i-1][j], result[i-1][j-1]) + 1\n            else: \n                result[i][j] = 0\n    m = result[0][0] \n    mij  = [0, 0] \n    for i in range(rows): \n        for j in range(cols): \n            if (m < result[i][j]): \n                m = result[i][j] \n                mij[0] = i \n                mij[1] = j \n  \n    return m, mij[0], mij[1]",
