    "instruction": "Generate an optimal solution for the given knapsack problem.",
    "input": "Weight:  10\nValue:   [60, 100, 120]\nWeight:  [2, 3, 4]",
    "output": "def knapsack(max_weight, values, weights):\n    sorted_index_list = sorted(range(len(weights)), key=lambda k: weights[k])\n    sorted_weights = [weights[i] for i in sorted_index_list]\n    sorted_values = [values[i] for i in sorted_index_list] \n   \n    result = [0]*len(sorted_weights)\n    value = 0\n\n    i = 0\n    while (max_weight > 0 and i < len(sorted_weights)):\n        if sorted_weights[i] <= max_weight: \n            result[i] = 1\n            value = value + sorted_values[i] \n            max_weight = max_weight - sorted_weights[i]\n        i += 1\n\n    return result, value\n\nmax_weight = 10\nvalues = [60, 100, 120]\nweights = [2, 3, 4]\n \noutput_result, output_value = knapsack(max_weight, values, weights)\nprint(\"The result of knapsack problem is: %s and value is %s\" %(output_result, output_value))",
    "category": "code_instruction"
