    "output": "#include <iostream> \n  \nusing namespace std; \n  \n// Function to remove duplicates from an array. \nvoid removeDuplicates(int arr[], int n) \n{ \n    // Take a temp array of size = n \n    int temp[n]; \n  \n    // Initialize temp array with 0 \n    memset(temp, 0, sizeof(temp)); \n  \n    // Do for each element of the original array \n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { \n  \n        // Check if the element is already seen \n        // before any index which is currently \n        // considered. \n        int j; \n        for (j = 0; j < i; j++) { \n            if (arr[i] == arr[j]) \n                break; \n        } \n  \n        // If not seen in any previous index then \n        // push it in the temp[] array. \n        if (j == i) \n            temp[k++] = arr[i]; \n    } \n  \n    // Now temp[] contains no duplicates. \n    // copy it in the original array \n    for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) \n        arr[i] = temp[i]; \n  \n    // resize original array \n    arr = realloc(arr, k * sizeof(arr[0])); \n} \n\nint arr[] = {1, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4}; \n  \nint n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]); \n  \nremoveDuplicates(arr, n); \n  \nfor (int i = 0; i < n; i++) \n    cout << arr[i] << \" \";",
