    "instruction": "Given an array of integers, can you create a function to partition the array into three parts such that the sum of each group is equal?",
    "input": "[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]",
    "output": "def sum_partition(arr):\n    sum_total = sum(arr)\n    if sum_total % 3 != 0:\n        return False\n\n    part_sum = sum_total / 3\n    left, right = 0, len(arr) - 1\n    cur_sum = 0\n \n    while right > left:\n        if cur_sum + arr[right] == part_sum:\n            cur_sum = 0\n            right -= 1\n        elif cur_sum + arr[right] > part_sum:\n            right -= 1\n        else:\n            cur_sum += arr[right]\n            right -= 1\n   \n    return True\n\nresult = sum_partition([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])\nprint(result)",
