    "instruction": "Can you write a method in Java which takes an array of elements and returns the longest increasing subsequence of that array?",
    "input": "[10, 21, 9, 33, 20, 50, 41, 60]",
    "output": "public class LongestIncreasingSubsequence {\n    public static int findLongestIncreasingSubsequence(int[] elements) {\n        int length = elements.length;\n\n        int[] dp = new int[length];\n        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) \n            dp[i] = 1; \n  \n        for (int i = 1; i < length; i++) \n            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) \n                if (elements[i] > elements[j] && dp[i] < dp[j] + 1) \n                    dp[i] = dp[j] + 1; \n\n        int max = 1; \n        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) \n            if (max < dp[i]) \n                max = dp[i]; \n  \n        return max;\n    }\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        int[] elements = {10, 21, 9, 33, 20, 50, 41, 60};\n        System.out.println(findLongestIncreasingSubsequence(elements));\n    }\n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
