    "instruction": "Create a function which finds the maximum profit for a given stock price data over a given period.",
    "input": "Stock prices = [11, 13, 8, 12, 15, 7, 10]",
    "output": "def findMaxProfit(stockPrices):\n    maxProfit = 0\n\n    for price in range(len(stockPrices)-1):\n        firstPrice = stockPrices[price]\n\n        for temp in range(price + 1, len(stockPrices)):\n            secondPrice = stockPrices[temp]\n            tempProfit = secondPrice - firstPrice\n            if (tempProfit > maxProfit):\n                maxProfit = tempProfit\n\n    return maxProfit\n\nstockPrices = [11, 13, 8, 12, 15, 7, 10]\nprint(\"Max Profit is:\", findMaxProfit(stockPrices))",
