    "instruction": "Compute a list of all permutations of a string.",
    "input": "string = 'ABC'",
    "output": "def permutations(string): \n    if len(string) == 0: \n        return [] \n  \n    if len(string) == 1: \n        return [string] \n  \n    perm_list = [] \n  \n    for i in range(len(string)): \n       m = string[i] \n       rem_string = string[:i] + string[i+1:] \n  \n       for perm in permutations(rem_string): \n           perm_list.append([m] + perm) \n  \n    return perm_list",
    "category": "code_instruction"
