    "output": "\"\"\"\nCreate an algorithm to detect the number of times a substring appears in a string\n\"\"\"\n\n# Function to detect the number of times a substring appears in a string\ndef detect_substring(s, t):\n    start = 0\n    cnt = 0\n\n    for _ in range(len(s)):\n        idx = s.find(t, start)\n       \n        # Check if substring exists\n        if idx != -1:\n            cnt += 1\n            start = idx + 1\n        else:\n            break\n   \n    return cnt\n\n# Test\ns = \"hello world\"\nt = \"lo\"\nprint(detect_substring(s, t))",
