    "instruction": "Create a Java program to delete duplicate elements from an array of integers.",
    "input": "[1, 9, 2, 8, 3, 7, 4, 6]",
    "output": "public class RemoveDuplicates { \n    public static int removeDuplicates(int arr[], int n) \n    { \n        if (n == 0 || n == 1) \n            return n; \n      \n        int[] temp = new int[n]; \n          \n        int j = 0; \n        for (int i=0; i<n-1; i++) \n            if (arr[i] != arr[i+1]) \n                temp[j++] = arr[i]; \n              \n        temp[j++] = arr[n-1];     \n       \n        for (int i=0; i<j; i++) \n            arr[i] = temp[i]; \n      \n        return j; \n    } \n  \n    public static void main (String[] args) { \n        int arr[] = {1, 9, 2, 8, 3, 7, 4, 6}; \n        int n = arr.length; \n       \n        n = removeDuplicates(arr, n); \n       \n        for (int i=0; i<n; i++) \n           System.out.print(arr[i]+\" \"); \n    } \n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
