    "instruction": "Create a Java algorithm to calculate the maximum subsequence sum of an array",
    "input": "nums = [-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4]",
    "output": "class maxSubsequenceSum \n{ \n    // Function to find the maximum subsequence sum in an array \n    public static int maxSubSum(int [] nums) \n    { \n        int max_so_far = nums[0]; \n        int max_ending_here = nums[0]; \n  \n        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) \n        { \n            max_ending_here = Math.max(max_ending_here + nums[i], nums[i]); \n\n            max_so_far = Math.max(max_so_far, max_ending_here); \n        } \n  \n        return max_so_far; \n    } \n      \n    // Main Method \n    public static void main(String args[]) \n    { \n        int [] nums = {-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4}; \n\n        System.out.println(\"Max Subsequence Sum: \"\n        + maxSubSum(nums)); \n    } \n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
