    "input": "arr[] = { 1, 2, 3, 4, 10 }\nsum = 14",
    "output": "public bool IsSumPairPresent(int[] arr, int sum) \n{ \n    // Create an empty map \n    Dictionary<int, int> map = new Dictionary<int, int>(); \n  \n    // Traverse through the given array \n    foreach (int val in arr) \n    { \n        // Check if pair (sum-arr[i]) already exists in map \n        // or not \n        if (!map.ContainsKey(sum - val)) \n            // Store sum-arr[i] in the map \n            map[val] = sum - val; \n  \n        else \n            // We've found a pair \n            return true; \n    } \n  \n    // No pair exists with given sum \n    return false; \n}",
