    "output": "public static int binarySearch(String[] arr, String target) {\n int low = 0;\n int high = arr.length - 1;\n \n while(low <= high) {\n int mid = (low + high)/2;\n if(arr[mid].equals(target)) {\n return mid;\n }\n else if(arr[mid].compareTo(target) < 0) {\n low = mid + 1;\n }\n else {\n high = mid - 1;\n }\n }\n \n return -1;\n}\n\n// Usage \n\nString[] arr = {'foo','bar','baz','quux'};\nint index = binarySearch(arr, 'bar');\n\nSystem.out.println(\"Target found at index: \" + index); // Target found at index: 1",
