    "output": "def linear_search(arr, x): \n    n = len(arr) \n  \n    # initializing start and end index \n    start = 0\n    end = n-1\n  \n    # Iterate while start not meets end \n    while start <= end: \n  \n        # Calculate mid index \n        mid = (start + end) // 2\n  \n        # Check if x is present at mid \n        if arr[mid] < x: \n            start = mid + 1\n  \n        # If x is greater, ignore left half \n        elif arr[mid] > x: \n            end = mid - 1\n  \n        # If x is smaller, ignore right half \n        else: \n            return mid \n  \n    return -1",
