    "output": "import math\n\n# vector a\nvec_a = (1,1)\n\n#vector b\nvec_b = (2,2)\n\n# calculate the dot product of the two vectors\ndot_product = 0\nfor i in range (len(vec_a)):\n    dot_product += vec_a[i]*vec_b[i]\n\n# calculate the magnitude of each vector\nmagnitude_a = 0\nfor i in range(len(vec_a)):\n    magnitude_a += vec_a[i]*vec_a[i]\n\nmagnitude_b = 0\nfor i in range(len(vec_b)):\n    magnitude_b += vec_b[i]*vec_b[i]\n  \n# calculate the angle\ncos_angle = dot_product/(math.sqrt(magnitude_a*magnitude_b))\nangle = math.degrees(math.acos(cos_angle))\n  \nprint(\"The angle between the two vectors is\", angle)",
