    "instruction": "Write a C++ program to find the longest substring in a given string that contains all the unique characters.",
    "input": "Sample string: \"abcdefghigklmnopqrstuvwxyz\"",
    "output": "#include<bits/stdc++.h>\n\n// Get the sample string\nstring str = \"abcdefghigklmnopqrstuvwxyz\";\n\n// Create a vector to store the start and end index of all the unique substrings\nvector<pair<int, int>> intervals;\n\n// Iterate through the characters\nint s = 0, e = -1;\nfor (int i = 0; i < str.length(); ++i) {\n  // Check if the character is already present\n  if (str[i] == str[e]) {\n    s = e + 1;\n    e = i;\n  } else {\n    // Update the start and end\n    s = i;\n    e = i;\n  }\n  \n  // Add the interval to the vector\n  intervals.push_back(make_pair(s, e));\n}\n\n// Iterate through the vector and find the longest interval\nint longestStart = -1, longestEnd = -1;\nint longestLen = 0;\nfor (auto interval : intervals) {\n  if (interval.second - interval.first > longestLen) {\n    longestLen = interval.second - interval.first;\n    longestStart = interval.first;\n    longestEnd = interval.second;\n  }\n}\n\n// Print the longest substring\ncout << \"The longest substring with all unique characters is '\";\nfor (int i = longestStart; i <= longestEnd; i++)\n  cout << str[i];\ncout << \"'\\n\";\n\n// Output: The longest substring with all unique characters is 'abcdefghi'",
    "category": "code_instruction"
