    "instruction": "Create a Java program to implement a simple stack. The stack should have push, pop, and peek methods.",
    "input": "Not applicable",
    "output": "public class Stack {\n \n private int[] data;\n private int top = -1;\n \n public Stack(int size) {\n data = new int[size];\n }\n \n public int pop() {\n if (top == -1) {\n throw new EmptyStackException();\n }\n return data[top--];\n }\n \n public void push(int element) {\n if (top == data.length - 1) {\n throw new FullStackException();\n }\n data[++top] = element;\n }\n \n public int peek() {\n if (top == -1) {\n throw new EmptyStackException();\n }\n return data[top];\n }\n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
