    "instruction": "Write a python program to merge two lists of integers into one sorted list without using the in-built sort function.",
    "input": "list1 = [3, 5, 9, 1, 8];\nlist2 = [4, 11, 7, 2];",
    "output": "def merge_sort(list1, list2): \n    merged_list = list1 + list2 \n    for i in range(len(merged_list)): \n        min_idx = i           \n        for j in range(i+1, len(merged_list)): \n            if merged_list[min_idx] > merged_list[j]: \n                min_idx = j \n        merged_list[i], merged_list[min_idx] = merged_list[min_idx], merged_list[i] \n    return merged_list \n  \nlist1 = [3, 5, 9, 1, 8] \nlist2 = [4, 11, 7, 2]\n  \nprint(merge_sort(list1, list2))",
    "category": "code_instruction"
