    "instruction": "Design a program to delete all duplicate elements from a sorted array in C.",
    "input": "[1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 4, 4, 5]",
    "output": "int removeDuplicates(int arr[], int n) \n{ \n    // Return, if array is empty \n    // or contains a single element \n    if (n == 0 || n == 1) \n        return n; \n  \n    int[] temp = new int[n]; \n  \n    // Start traversing elements \n    int j = 0; \n    for (int i = 0; i < n-1; i++) \n        // If current element is not equal \n        // to next element then store that \n        // current element \n        if (arr[i] != arr[i+1]) \n            temp[j++] = arr[i]; \n  \n    // Store the last element as whether \n    // it is unique or repeated, it hasn't \n    // stored previously \n    temp[j++] = arr[n-1]; \n  \n    // Modify original array \n    for (int i=0; i<j; i++) \n        arr[i] = temp[i]; \n  \n    return j; \n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
