    "output": "import numpy as np \n\ndef optimize_portfolio(profits, risks):\n    '''\n    Function to optimize the portfolio of stocks given expected profits and risks\n    '''\n    # Algorithm to get the optimal weights\n    expected_returns = np.array(profits)/np.sum(profits)\n    risks = np.array(risks) / np.sum(risks)\n    optimal_weights = np.multiply(expected_returns, risks)\n    return optimal_weights\n  \nprofits = [8, 9, 5, 10]\nrisks = [2, 3, 1 ,4]\nweights = optimize_portfolio(profits, risks)\nprint(weights)",
