    "instruction": "Given a collection of 2D points, generate a convex hull.",
    "input": "[[3,2], [5,4], [2,7], [9,6]]",
    "output": "def convex_hull(points): \n  \n    # get leftmost point \n    min_x = float(\"inf\") \n    min_pt = () \n    for pt in points: \n        if pt[0] < min_x: \n            min_x = pt[0] \n            min_pt = pt \n  \n    hull_pts = [] \n  \n    current_pt = min_pt \n    hull_pts.append(current_pt) \n  \n    # iterate through points in a loop \n    while True: \n  \n        next_pt = points[0] \n        for pt in points[1:]:  \n            # See if the new point is counterclockwise of the last point \n            val = orientation(current_pt, next_pt, pt)  \n  \n            # If so, the next point  \n            # is the farthest point \n            if val > 0: \n                next_pt = pt \n          \n        current_pt = next_pt \n        hull_pts.append(current_pt) \n  \n        # If all the points have been processed,  \n        # the loop terminates  \n        if current_pt == min_pt: \n            break\n  \n    return hull_pts",
