    "instruction": "Create an algorithm to solve 8-puzzle using A* search.",
    "input": "",
    "output": "def a_star_search(startState, goalState): \n\topenSet = {startState}:  # Set of node to consider \n\tclosedSet = set()        # set of already considered nodes\n\tgScore = {startState : 0} # distance from start to node\n\tfScore = {startState : heuristic(startState, goalState)} # estimated distance from start to goal\n \n\twhile openSet != set(): \n\t\tcurrent = findMin(openSet, fScore)\t# node with lowest fScore from openSet  \n\t\tif current == goalState:\n\t\t\treturn reconstructPath(current) \n\n\t\topenSet.remove(current)\n\t\tclosedSet.add(current)\n\n\t\tfor neighbor in neighbors(current): \n\t\t\tif neighbor in closedSet: \n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n \n\t\t\tnewGscore = gScore[current] + distance(current,neighbor)\n\t\t\tif neighbor not in openSet: \n\t\t\t\topenSet.add(neighbor)\n\t\t\telif newGscore >= gScore[neighbor]: \n\t\t\t\tcontinue # This is not better path\n\n\t\t\t# This path is the best path till now\n\t\t\tgScore[neighbor] = newGscore\n\t\t\tfScore[neighbor] = gScore[neighbor] + heuristic(neighbor, goalState)\n\n\t# No path possible \n\treturn failure",
