    "instruction": "Generate a JavaScript program that calculates the mean, mode, median, and range of a set of numbers.",
    "input": "[50, 23, 56, 10, 30, 70]",
    "output": "let input = [50, 23, 56, 10, 30, 70];\n\nconst getMean = arr => {\n let sum = arr.reduce((a, b) => a + b);\n return sum/arr.length;\n}\n\nconst getMode = arr => {\n let modeValue = 0;\n let modeCount = 0;\n arr.forEach(num => {\n  let count = 0;\n  arr.forEach(x => {\n   if (x == num) count++;\n  });\n  if (count > modeCount) {\n   modeValue = num;\n   modeCount = count;\n  } \n });\n return modeValue;\n}\n\nconst getMedian = arr => {\n let sorted = arr.sort((a,b) => a-b);\n let middle = Math.floor(sorted.length/2);\n if (sorted.length % 2 !== 0 ) return sorted[middle];\n else return (sorted[middle - 1] + sorted[middle]) / 2;\n}\n\nconst getRange = arr => {\n let numMax = Math.max(...arr);\n let numMin = Math.min(...arr);\n return numMax - numMin;\n}\n\nlet mean = getMean(input);\nlet mode = getMode(input);\nlet median = getMedian(input);\nlet range = getRange(input);\n\nconsole.log(`Mean: ${mean}, Mode: ${mode}, Median: ${median}, Range: ${range}`);",
    "category": "code_instruction"
