    "input": "Given an undirected graph G with vertices V and edges E. Design an algorithm to pick a vertex v that has the most edges in G.",
    "output": "def mostEdgesVertex(G, V, E):\n    # create an empty dictionary\n    d = {}\n    for v in V:\n        d[v] = 0\n    \n    # loop through edges and store v, e pair in dict\n    for e in E:\n        (v1, v2) = e\n        d[v1] += 1\n        d[v2] += 1\n    \n    # find max value in dict\n    maxValue = -1\n    maxVertex = \"none\"\n    \n    for v in V:\n        if maxValue < d[v]:\n            maxValue = d[v]\n            maxVertex = v\n    \n    # return vertex with max edges\n    return maxVertex",
