    "instruction": "Find the minimum number of coins that can make a certain amount.",
    "input": "Amount: 13",
    "output": "\"\"\"\nFind the minimum number of coins that can make a certain amount.\n\"\"\"\n\nCOINS = [1, 5, 10, 25]\n \ndef min_coins(amount):\n    if amount == 0:\n        return 0\n    res = float(\"inf\") \n    for i in range(len(COINS)):\n        if COINS[i] <= amount:\n            sub_res = min_coins(amount-COINS[i]) \n            if sub_res != float(\"inf\") and sub_res + 1 < res: \n                res = sub_res + 1\n    return res\n \nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    amount = 13\n    print(min_coins(amount))",
