    "instruction": "Generate a program in Java that takes an array of integers and returns an array containing the squares of all even numbers in the original array.",
    "input": "[1, 4, 6, 8, 9, 10]",
    "output": "import java.util.Arrays;\n\npublic class SquareEvenNumbers {\n public static int[] squareEvenNumbers(int[] arr) {\n int[] resultArr = new int[arr.length];\n int resultIndex = 0;\n \n for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {\n  if (arr[i] % 2 == 0)\n   resultArr[resultIndex++] = arr[i] * arr[i];\n }\n \n return Arrays.copyOf(resultArr, resultIndex);\n }\n \n public static void main(String[] args) {\n int[] arr = { 1, 4, 6, 8, 9, 10 };\n int[] resultArr = squareEvenNumbers(arr);\n \n System.out.println(Arrays.toString(resultArr));\n }\n}\n\n# Output\n[16, 36, 64, 100]",
