    "instruction": "Create a Java program that displays a calendar for any given year.",
    "input": "Not applicable",
    "output": "import java.util.Calendar;\nimport java.util.GregorianCalendar;\n\npublic class PrintCalendar {\n\n public static void main(String[] args) {\n  int year = 2021;\n  printCalendar(year);\n }\n\n public static void printCalendar(int year) {\n  // Create a GregorianCalendar object with\n  // the specified year and month\n  Calendar cal = new GregorianCalendar(year, 0, 1);\n\n  // Get the number of days in that month\n  int days = cal.getActualMaximum(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH);\n\n  // Print the calendar header\n  System.out.println(\"          \" + cal.getDisplayName(Calendar.MONTH, Calendar.LONG, Locale.ENGLISH)\n    + \" \" + cal.get(Calendar.YEAR));\n  System.out.println(\"-----------------------------\");\n  System.out.println(\" Sun Mon Tue Wed Thu Fri Sat\");\n\n  // Print the calendar body\n  for (int i = 1; i < cal.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_WEEK); i++) {\n   System.out.print(\"    \");\n  }\n  for (int i = 1; i <= days; i++) {\n   System.out.printf(\"%4d\", i);\n\n   if (i % 7 == 0) {\n    System.out.println();\n   }\n  }\n\n  System.out.println();\n }\n}",
    "category": "code_instruction"
