    "output": "// There are three pins: source, destination, and auxiliary\n// Move n disks from source to destination, using auxiliary as needed\nfunction moveDisks(n, source, destination, auxiliary) {\n  // Base case - nothing to do\n  if (n === 0) {\n    return;\n  }\n    \n  // Move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary\n  moveDisks(n-1, source, auxiliary, destination);\n\n  // Move the nth disk from source to destination\n  console.log(\"Move disk\", n, \"from\", source, \"to\", destination);\n\n  // Move n-1 disks from auxiliary to destination\n  moveDisks(n-1, auxiliary, destination, source);\n}\n\n// Begin the program with three disks on source\nmoveDisks(3, \"Source\", \"Destination\", \"Auxiliary\");",
