    "instruction": "Generate a program that sorts a matrix of integers.",
    "input": "[[10, 8, 5], \n[7, 2 ,1], \n[9, 4, 3]]",
    "output": "def sort_matrix(m):\n    # We will use bubble sort to sort the matrix\n    for i in range(len(m)): \n        for j in range(0, len(m[0])-i-1): \n            if m[i][j] > m[i][j+1] : \n                m[i][j], m[i][j+1] = m[i][j+1], m[i][j] \n  \n    # iterate through row\n    for i in range(len(m)): \n        for j in range(len(m[0])): \n            # bubble sort column wise\n            for row in range(len(m)-1):\n                if (m[row][j] > m[row+1][j]): \n                    # swap the elements \n                    m[row][j],m[row+1][j] = m[row+1][j],m[row][j]\n    return m",
    "category": "code_instruction"
