    "instruction": "Write a JavaScript function that takes two strings and checks if they are different by exactly one character.",
    "input": "String 1: googleg\nString 2: google",
    "output": "function oneDifference(str1, str2) {\n  // check the lengths, if they are more than 1 character off, return false\n  if (Math.abs(str1.length - str2.length) > 1) {\n    return false;\n  }\n \n  // loop through each character in the strings, looking for one difference\n  let diffCount = 0;\n  for (let i = 0; i < str1.length; i++) {\n    if (str1[i] !== str2[i]) {\n      // if the difference count is already > 0, there must be more than one difference so return false\n      if (diffCount > 0) {\n        return false;\n      } else {\n        diffCount++;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n \n  // there can be only one difference, if we reach this far, we passed\n  return true;\n}",
