    "instruction": "Design a program to solve linear equations",
    "input": "x + 2y = 4",
    "output": "def solveLinearEquations(eq):\n    terms = eq.split(\" \")\n    if terms[1] == \"+\":\n        x = (int(terms[4]) - int(terms[3][:-1])) / int(terms[0][:-1])\n        y = (int(terms[4]) - int(terms[0][:-1])) / int(terms[3][:-1])\n    elif terms[1] == \"-\":\n        x = (int(terms[4]) + int(terms[3][:-1])) / int(terms[0][:-1])\n        y = (int(terms[0][:-1]) - int(terms[4])) / int(terms[3][:-1])\n    return (x, y)",
    "category": "code_instruction"
