    "output": "def rearrange_chars(string):\n  # create seperate lists to store different characters\n  lowercase = []\n  uppercase = []\n  numbers = []\n  \n  # loop through the string\n  for char in string:\n    # add to appropriate list\n    if char.islower():\n        lowercase.append(char)\n    elif char.isupper():\n        uppercase.append(char)\n    else: # includes numbers\n        numbers.append(char)\n  # join the lists together\n  rearranged_string = \"\".join(lowercase + uppercase + numbers)\n  return rearranged_string\n\n# test\nstring = \"HelloWorld123\"\nprint(rearrange_chars(string)) # prints 'ellohWrdL123'",
