    "instruction": "Create a neural network in TensorFlow for multiclass classification tasks.",
    "input": "Not applicable",
    "output": "import tensorflow as tf\nimport numpy as np\n\n# define the dimensions\nnum_classes = 3\ninput_dim = 2\n\n# placeholders for the data \nX = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, shape=(None, input_dim))\nY = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, shape=(None, num_classes))\n\n# weights and bias\nW = tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([input_dim, num_classes]))\nb = tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([1, num_classes]))\n\n# output\nlogits = tf.add(tf.matmul(X, W), b)\n\n# define the cost calculation\ncost = tf.reduce_mean(tf.nn.softmax_cross_entropy_with_logits_v2(logits=logits, labels=Y))\n\n# define the optimization to find min cost\noptimizer = tf.train.GradientDescentOptimizer(learning_rate=0.01).minimize(cost)\n\n# define the prediction\ny_pred = tf.nn.softmax(logits=logits)\n\n# define the accuracy calculation\ncorrect_prediction = tf.equal(tf.argmax(y_pred, 1), tf.argmax(Y, 1))\naccuracy = tf.reduce_mean(tf.cast(correct_prediction, tf.float32))\n\n# initialize the variables\ninit = tf.global_variables_initializer()",
